\pard\keep\keepn\widctlpar\s2\sb40\sl252\slmult1\cf1\f2\fs26 Explanation of symbols\par

\pard\nowidctlpar\sa200\sl276\slmult1\cf0\f1\fs22 C1: Low-level 6301 emulation on Keyboard/Mouse option page\par
C2: High-level software overscan emulation\par
This isn't listed for demos because there are too many cases. It is listed for games, but pirated games with an overscan intro aren't listed.\par
When you use C2, some border is generally recommended too.\par
DI: there are bad disk images around \par
HIRES: program can run in monochrome\par
STF or STE: select in Machine option 'ST model'\par
T1XX where X are digits: TOS version\par
WU: ST Video option \i GLU Wakeup\i0  (1-4)\par
US: ST Video option Unstable Shifter\par
WP: write-protect the disk\par
There are 2 different ways in Steem, depending on whether the disk is in a ZIP or RAR archive or not.\par
If it is the case, uncheck Read/Write Archives in the disk manager options.\par
If not, right click and check Read Only.\par
ADAT: Disk Manager option \i Turbo Drive\i0  unchecked\par
No B: disconnect drive B in Disk Manager\par
60Hz: the game apparently can operate at 60Hz, which can be interesting if you want to use VSync with a 60Hz monitor. Note there are certainly many more, it's not a complete list at all.\par
MSTE: Mega STE\par
